      "message": "Yes, we scale the shader\u0027s output by alpha before applying color filters, shader-\u003ealpha-\u003efilter.  Back in PS1 where I just called SkShader::makeWithColorFilter(), we got the effect of shader-\u003efilter-\u003ealpha instead, and that\u0027s not always the same.\n\nSkShader::makeWithColorFilter() still kind of technically does what it says on the tin, but you _can\u0027t_ replace a shader and color filter with it when the paint has transparency.  So it\u0027s possible and kind of likely that every other use of makeWithColorFilter() has this bug...",
